explanation:
The assimilation policy in French West Africa failed primarily because many Africans resisted being culturally assimilated into French norms and values. They wanted to retain their own cultural identities and resist the imposition of foreign cultural practices.
These are some of the other reasons the French Policy of Assimilation failed;
1. The varied African cultures made it difficult for them to be absorbed into the French culture2. The Africans were not able to get the French type of education3. The Africans were not willing to become Christians4. They forced opposition from the Muslims5. The French did not compete with the Africans for cabinet posts and commercial activities6. African traditional rulers feared they would lose their position7. French traders feared competition, so they opposed the system8. It was expensive to implement the system because of the vastness of the French empire.
